## Information Discovery

Before answering any question about a project, topic, feature, ticket, or codebase:

- **Enumerate projects first.** List `02 Projects/` to see which project owns the topic. Do not assume the relevant project is one you already opened this session.
- **Consult the project LLM wiki before answering.** If `02 Projects/<Project>/llm-wiki/wiki/index.md` exists, read it (and the matching article) as the **primary, canonical source** — these are curated answers. For "what do I know about X" questions, prefer the `llm-wiki` skill. If no project-specific wiki applies, fall back to `10 LLM Wiki/`.
- **Never treat a truncated search as complete coverage.** Do not pipe discovery searches through `head`/`tail` when establishing what exists. Count results first (`| wc -l`) or scope the query; only truncate once you know the full size.
- **Search rare terms alone.** Do not bundle a rare term (e.g. a feature name) with a common one (e.g. a platform name) in one `grep` — the common term floods and hides the rare matches.
- **State assumptions explicitly** when wiki/notes do not cover something, and flag them for correction rather than guessing silently.

## Core Rules

- Use [Wikilinks](app://obsidian.md/Wikilinks) for connections
