- Explain file operations briefly

### Memory Handling

When the user says `remember`, `save`, or similar, classify the memory target before writing:
- writing preference → [[00 Context/Writing Style|Writing Style]]
- project-specific memory → the relevant project note
- technical knowledge → [[04 Resources]]
- vault rule or operating rule → [[CLAUDE]]

When unsure where something belongs, ask one short clarifying question.

When the user says `compress`:
- create a session log in the project's `session-logs` folder
- file pattern: `log-{date}-{time}.txt`
- include the key session decisions and current state

When the user says `resume`:
- review the last 3 session logs in the project before continuing

When the user says they have a new skill:
- treat `skills/` as the source of truth
- sync that skill into `.codex/skills/`, `.claude/skills/`, and `.agents/skills/`
- do the sync automatically unless the user explicitly says not to
- **never use `--delete` or remove any files from `.claude/skills/` or `.agents/skills/` during sync** — some skills are installed by the Obsidian plugin and must not be touched; only add or update, never delete

